<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3955] HintedHandoff won&apos;t compact a single sstable, resulting in repeated log messages</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3955</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;First introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3554&quot; title=&quot;Hints are not replayed unless node was marked down&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3554&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3554&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and then mostly solved in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3733&quot; title=&quot;Once a host has been hinted to, log messages for it repeat every 10 mins even if no hints are delivered&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3733&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3733&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, there is still one special case where the HH log message will repeat every 10 mins for 0 rows: when there have previously been hints delivered to the node, but now only a single sstable exists.  Because the we refused to compact a single sstable, and it contains tombstones for the hints, the message repeats.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
